WEBVTT

00:08:56.500 --> 00:09:00.063
And then the Borg
assimilated the deaf guy --

00:09:00.087 --> 00:09:02.849
not out of pity, not out of anger,

00:09:02.873 --> 00:09:06.174
but because he had
a biological distinctiveness

00:09:06.198 --> 00:09:07.764
that the Borg wanted,

00:09:07.788 --> 00:09:10.936
including unique language capabilities.

00:09:11.599 --> 00:09:13.639
I would much rather see that commercial.

00:09:13.663 --> 00:09:14.813
(Laughter)

00:09:15.866 --> 00:09:19.527
Why does thinking about ability
make people so uncomfortable?

00:09:20.224 --> 00:09:23.108
You might know a play, later a movie,

00:09:23.132 --> 00:09:24.982
called "Children of a Lesser God,"

00:09:25.006 --> 00:09:26.846
by Mark Medoff.

00:09:26.870 --> 00:09:28.579
That play, that title,

00:09:28.603 --> 00:09:32.065
actually comes from a poem
by Alfred Tennyson,